    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-03-24T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-03-24T18:00:00-05:00" n="516"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d516">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/4169: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-03-25T01:00:00+02:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 25, 1919, 1 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 7:57 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2729. Department’s circular of March 8, 7 [<hi rend="italic">6</hi>] p.m.<note
                        n="36" xml:id="d516fn36">See telegram to the Ambassador in Great Britain,
                        no. 4773, Mar. 8, 6 p.m., <ref target="#pg_478">p. 478</ref>.</note> Foreign
                    Office informs me Italian Consul at Vladivostok has been authorized to make
                    similar representations to Omsk Government, provided other Allied
                    representatives receive like instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nelson Page</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
